subSubSection.paragraph:
Etymology
. The specific epithet honours Carl Ludwig Koch (
1778–1857
) and his son Ludwig Carl Christian Koch (
1825–1908
), both eminent German arachnologists and contributors to the taxonomy of the Australian arachnofauna.

Prosoma
. Length 8.5, width 6.5; reddish-brown with genus-specific Union-Jack pattern and distinct median and irregular marginal light bands (
Fig. 15A
); sternum black (
Fig. 15C
).

Opisthosoma. Length 6.8, width 4.6; dorsally with dark folium pattern that is bordered by light setae (
Fig. 15A
); venter black (
Fig. 15C
).

Pedipalps. Cymbium dorsally with dense layer of silvery setae; tip with 5–7 macrosetae ( Figs 15E–F ); tegular apophysis ridge about three quarters of tegular apophysis width, almost straight ( Figs 6B , 15J–K ); embolus very thin along its length and slightly curved apically; terminal apophysis broad, sickle-shaped ( Figs 7B ,
15I
).

